# Architecture Pattern: MVVM (Model-View-ViewModel)

This project follows the MVVM pattern with the following data flow:
**View → ViewModel (Controller) → Store → Provider → Service**

## Key Architectural Rules

- Each View (Page/Component) must use only ONE corresponding ViewModel (Controller)
- Any ViewModel can be used by many Views
- ViewModels may use many Stores or Services, but must NOT use other ViewModels
- Stores can only import Providers and other Stores
- Providers can only import Services
- Services can only import other Services

## Dependency Injection

- Use InversifyJS for dependency injection
- All dependencies are registered in `src/dependencies.ts`
- Binding symbols are defined in `src/bindings.ts`
- Controllers must be decorated with `@injectable()`
- Use `@inject(Bindings.XXX)` for injecting dependencies

## Boundaries Rules (Import Restrictions)

### Pages can import:
- Components
- Their own controller (same folder)
- Shared controllers (from `views/controllers/`)
- Hooks

### Components can import:
- Other Components
- Their own controller (same folder)
- Shared controllers (from `views/controllers/`)
- Hooks

### Controllers can import:
- Stores only

### Stores can import:
- Providers
- Other Stores

### Providers can import:
- Services only

### Services can import:
- Other Services only
